<br>
Also wouldnt mind to see diffrent pet buffs then just burnout and velocity.  Sure were not a buffing class but sheesh come on we should be at least be able to do some type of buffing or raise there level with spells.  Im not asking for anything unreasonable as far as buffs, I dont wanna buff him for over 200 str/dex etc or give him 700 dmg procs andI dont wanna raise my pets lvl to be red con or anything, just so it isnt teal heh. I just want a reasonable few pet buffs some things that make them have innate procs of diffrent types.  If were the masters of summoning why cant we mix pets abilitys?  <br>
<br>
Anyone else think it sux that epic pet is teal at 62? ;/ put a few months of work into epic for it to go teal at 62 hehe. <br>
<br>
Another thing I wouldnt mind to see is a few more Wrath of the element type spells for us.  Fire based dot would be nice but a small upgrade on the dmg of them nothing major but a 1200 or 1300 fire based dot would be nice even if it was over a 2 minute duration or something.  I know we arent a dot class but we do get some dot's that are already for 800 some dmg I dont think a 400 dmg increase and diffrent resist check is over powering.<br>
<br>
Lastly please give us some useful summoned equipment, ive had talisman of return for awhile now and only people who use it are bards cause there bugged and it doesnt do a component check on them.  Like it was posted above a upgrade to waterstone coldstone and ring of levi would rock maybe 1 that does all 3 of those at the same time.  Pet weapons rock love em, belt/girdle of the magikot is nice.  Our focus items are fine I can deal with the loss of stats for a summoned item, but for crying out loud take the component use off of talisman of return!.<br>
<br>
